  "wikitext": "\n'''2-6-095\n\nThe first mark (or buoy) seen by an observer approaching the land from the open sea.\n\nIt usually serves to indicate the seaward approach to a harbour, river or estuary.\n\n[[Image:Ch2_Fig53.jpg|400px|border]]\n\n\nNote: In the U.S.A. this is also sometimes called a Sea-Buoy.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Landfall Mark (or Buoy)}}\n[[Category:2.6 Visual Aids in general: Buoyage and Beaconage]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
